message: Update GitHub Actions workflow for Playwright deployment: modify the 'deploy' job to ensure it only runs on the main branch and streamline job dependencies for improved clarity and maintainability.

Add best practices documentation for Playwright test steps and implement reusable step patterns

This commit introduces a comprehensive guide on best practices for structuring test steps in Playwright, enhancing readability, maintainability, and debugging efficiency. It includes examples of step organization, naming conventions, and verification practices. Additionally, reusable step functions are implemented in the ProductSteps class to encapsulate common interactions with the Products page, promoting code reuse and clarity in test cases. The changes also include an index file for easier import of step classes.

Remove browser installation analysis script and streamline Playwright GitHub Actions workflow: eliminate caching checks and analysis steps for Chrome installation, focusing on a direct installation approach with improved reporting of installed browser version. This update simplifies the workflow while maintaining essential functionality.

Enhance browser installation analysis in GitHub Actions: add detailed cache structure output, verify Chrome installation, and improve cache key management to include Playwright configuration. Introduce checks for browser directory permissions and installation success, ensuring better debugging and reporting for Playwright browser setups.

Enhance GitHub Actions workflow for Playwright: improve Chrome browser installation process by adding caching checks and performance timing. Introduce analysis step to evaluate installation duration, ensuring efficient dependency management and clearer reporting of installation metrics.

Enhance test metadata management and reporting: add utility for standardized test metadata, implement custom metadata reporter for console output, and introduce new test scripts with metadata integration. Update package.json with new test commands for filtering by metadata. Additionally, create comprehensive documentation on test metadata usage and best practices.

Enhance report generation script: add duration parsing function to HTML report rendering, improving the accuracy of displayed test durations. This update ensures that duration data is correctly processed and included in the generated reports.

Enhance report generation script and GitHub Actions workflow: implement a line chart for visualizing test durations in HTML reports, improving data representation. Update CSS styles for data points and labels to enhance user interaction and clarity. Add grid lines to the chart for better readability and integrate build duration calculation in the workflow for accurate reporting.

Refactor report generation script and GitHub Actions workflow: update max duration calculation to use a namespace for improved clarity, enhance error handling in the script execution, and simplify build duration handling in the workflow for better maintainability.

Refactor report generation script and GitHub Actions workflow: adjust CSS styles for history grid in HTML reports to enhance visual clarity and user experience. Update Slack notification format to include detailed test run information, improving communication of test results.
